remarks: A kind of Aristotelian inference.  This judgement replaces the mode of inference ~ barbara when the minor premise has a general context. Proposition 65 of [Frege1879] p. 53.  (Contributed by RP, 17-Apr-2020.) (Proof modification is discouraged.)
statement: frege65a $p |- ( ( ( ps -> ch ) /\ ( ta -> et ) ) -> ( ( ( ch -> th ) /\ ( et -> ze ) ) -> ( if- ( ph , ps , ta ) -> if- ( ph , th , ze ) ) ) ) $.
